text: I remember in 2021 there was like a giant line for Covid PCR testing and you had to show a vaccination certificate to enter the building and yet most of my classes were in tiny rooms with all the windows closed and people came there sick because you still had to make up absences.

It's genuinely sad that after all that useless retardation with masks, hand sanitizers, and flu vaccines, the two actual things that prevent disease spread, always keeping a window open and actually not going to work when you're sick and staying home are still just not practiced.

When we did go wfh there was a period we had no zoom classes because no one here knew what zoom was so we just got a file depository with a bunch of PDFs and they told us figure it out. Best time in my uni life
